Certainly! In LaTeX, you can automatically generate a table of contents (TOC) using the `\tableofcontents` command. Below is a simple example of a LaTeX document that includes a table of contents, sections, and subsections.

```latex
\documentclass{article}

\title{Example Document with Table of Contents}
\author{Your Name}
\date{\today}

\begin{document}

\maketitle

% Generate the table of contents
\tableofcontents
\newpage

% Define sections and subsections
\section{Introduction}
This is the introduction section.

\section{Methodology}
\subsection{Data Collection}
This subsection describes how data was collected.

\subsection{Data Analysis}
This subsection outlines the data analysis methods used.

\section{Results}
This section presents the results of the study.

\section{Conclusion}
This section summarizes the findings and conclusions drawn from the study.

\end{document}
```

### Explanation of the key commands:

1. **`\documentclass{article}`**: This command specifies the document class. The `article` class is commonly used for short documents like articles, reports, and essays.

2. **`\title`, `\author`, `\date`**: These commands define the title, author, and date of the document, which are displayed on the title page.

3. **`\maketitle`**: This command generates the title page using the information provided by `\title`, `\author`, and `\date`.

4. **`\tableofcontents`**: This command generates the table of contents, which lists all sections and subsections with their corresponding page numbers.

5. **`\newpage`**: This command starts a new page after the table of contents.

6. **`\section` and `\subsection`**: These commands define sections and subsections, respectively. LaTeX automatically numbers these sections and includes them in the table of contents.

### Compiling the Document
To generate the PDF with the table of contents, you need to compile the LaTeX document twice. The first compilation generates the necessary `.toc` file, and the second compilation includes the table of contents in the PDF. You can use any LaTeX editor or command-line tools like `pdflatex` to compile the document:

```bash
pdflatex your_document.tex
pdflatex your_document.tex
```

Replace `your_document.tex` with the name of your LaTeX file. After running these commands, you will have a PDF file with a table of contents that accurately reflects the structure of your document.

